     Comments     : The  Terrorists  virus  works  like the BGS9-Virus and
                    in  fact  there are very similar routines between BGS9
                    and Terrorists. 


                    The virus allocates some Chip memory and copies itself
                    in  that  allocated  memory area. To stay resident the
                    virus  uses the KICK-Vectors. After the next reset the
                    OpenWindow()-Vector from the intuition.library will be
                    patched.


                    If  you  are  now  booting with an unprotected disk or
                    your HD!. The virus will first forbid all your System-
                    Requesters.  That  means no requester telling "Disk is
                    Write-Protected"  or  something  like that will pop up
                    now. 


                    Then  the  virus  scans the first file in the startup-
                    sequence  to move this file into the Root-Dir with the
                    invisible name: $A0202020A02020A020A0A0. Now the virus
                    file  will  be  created  with the original name of the
                    1.st loaded programm in the startup-sequence. 


                    The  next time your are booting with the infected disk
                    the  virus  will  start the original file after it had
                    installed itself in memory. So be careful.

                    After  every infection the virus checks for a value in
                    $DFF007.  If  this  register  contains  this  value  a
                    GFX-Message   will be shown with the following message
                    written in big capital letters:


                    THE NAMES HAVE BEEN CHANGED TO PROTECT THE INNOCENT...
                    THE  TERRORISTS  HAVE YOU UNDER CONTROL. EVERYTHING IS
                    DESTROYED YOUR SYSTEM IS INFECTED THERE IS NO HOPE FOR
                    BETTER TIMES. THE FIRST TERRORISTS VIRUS!!!


